---
// Pillars - Six pillars of Intelligent Economics
---

<section class="pillars section" id="pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="pillars__intro">
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="section-label">The Architecture</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Six pillars of Intelligent Economics</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <p class="section-body">
          This framework is not a top-down mandate. It is a physics — a science of nucleation that begins with small, successful "Symbiotic Zones" and propagates through overwhelmingly successful imitation. Each pillar is a necessary component of the whole.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <a href="#volunteer" class="btn btn--primary" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">Help Build It</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars__grid">
      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">01</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="14" width="4" height="7" rx="1" fill="#00ff88" opacity="0.9"/>
            <rect x="10" y="9" width="4" height="12" rx="1" fill="#00ff88" opacity="0.7"/>
            <rect x="17" y="4" width="4" height="17" rx="1" fill="#00ff88" opacity="0.5"/>
            <line x1="2" y1="21.5" x2="22" y2="21.5" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Replace the GDP Loss Function</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          GDP is criminally insane — it counts cancer treatments as growth. The MIND Dashboard replaces it: Material × Intelligence × Network × Diversity. A zero in any capital means total systemic failure, so the system incentivizes balance.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">MIND Dashboard</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">02</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Seedling / geometry -->
            <path d="M12 20 L12 10" stroke="#7b4bff" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M12 14 C12 14 7 12 6 7 C10 7 13 10 12 14Z" fill="#7b4bff" opacity="0.8"/>
            <path d="M12 10 C12 10 17 9 18 4 C14 4 11 7 12 10Z" fill="#7b4bff" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Geometry Engineering</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          The state transitions from extractor to gardener. Rather than mandates, policy reshapes the economic landscape so that desirable outcomes become the natural path of least resistance — carving channels, not issuing commands.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">Policy as Physics</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">03</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Diamond / dual currency -->
            <polygon points="12,3 20,9 12,21 4,9" fill="none" stroke="#00c8ff" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <polyline points="4,9 12,12 20,9" stroke="#00c8ff" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linejoin="round" opacity="0.6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">Dual-Currency System</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          Foundation Coins (hard money, tethered to computation) for the scarce Atomic Economy. Culture Credits (flow money with demurrage) for the abundant Bit Economy. Two currencies for two physical realities.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">Monetary Architecture</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">04</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Balance scale / guardian lattice -->
            <line x1="12" y1="3" x2="12" y2="20" stroke="#ffb400" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="5" y1="6" x2="19" y2="6" stroke="#ffb400" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M5 6 L3 11 C3 13 7 13 7 11 Z" fill="none" stroke="#ffb400" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <path d="M19 6 L21 11 C21 13 17 13 17 11 Z" fill="none" stroke="#ffb400" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="9" y1="20" x2="15" y2="20" stroke="#ffb400" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">The Guardian Lattice</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          Machine-speed governance: AI Oracles monitor the MIND dashboard and adjust friction or flow automatically. Human Juries (randomly selected Oracle Councils) provide the Alignment Layer. The algorithm proposes; humanity disposes.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">Adaptive Governance</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">05</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Cycle / adaptive governance -->
            <path d="M4 12 A8 8 0 0 1 20 12" stroke="#ff6482" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
            <path d="M20 12 A8 8 0 0 1 4 12" stroke="#ff6482" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none" opacity="0.5"/>
            <polyline points="17,8 20,12 24,10" stroke="#ff6482" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <polyline points="7,16 4,12 0,14" stroke="#ff6482" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">The Dual Engine of Change</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          The Fast Engine: visible market tactics and price adjustments. The Slow Engine: the invisible evolution of institutions and cultural norms. Policies must account for how intelligent agents anticipate and game new rules — the Lucas Critique.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">Feedback Modeling</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card glow-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="pillar-card__num">06</div>
        <div class="pillar-card__icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Symbiotic zone / network node -->
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3" fill="none" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.8"/>
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="7" fill="none" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3 2"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="3" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="19" y1="12" x2="21" y2="12" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="19" x2="12" y2="21" stroke="#00ff88" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="pillar-card__title">The Nucleation Strategy</h3>
        <p class="pillar-card__body">
          Not a global flip of the switch — but Florences of the 21st Century. Protected Symbiotic Zones prove the model. Their demonstrable resilience and fulfillment make the old extractive world obsolete through imitation, not mandate.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar-card__tag">Symbiotic Blueprint</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { initClipWipes, initScrollReveals } from '../scripts/gsap-reveals';

  initClipWipes();
  initScrollReveals();
</script>
